    <abstract>
      <t>The network packet format used by NTP has changed very little
	between NTPv1, defined by <xref target="RFC0958">RFC 958</xref> in
	1985, and NTPv4, defined by <xref target="RFC5905">RFC 5905</xref>.
	The core network packet used by NTP has no spare bits available for
	reporting additional state information and no larger data areas
	available for larger amounts of information.  This proposal offers a
	new extension field that would contains this additional
	information.</t>
    </abstract>
