  <middle>
    <section title="Introduction">
      <t>The core NTP packet format has changed little
	since <xref target="RFC0958">RFC 958</xref> was published in 1985.
	Since then, there has been demonstrated need to convey additional
	information about NTP's state in an NTP packet, but no
	backward-compatible way to usurp the few otherwise potentially
	available bits has been found, and no larger data areas are
	available in the core packet structure.  This proposal offers a new
	extension field that would contain this additional information.</t>

      <section title="Requirements Language">
